## StoryApp Backend ##

A Spring Boot REST API for managing stories with authentication, role-based authorization, publishing system, pagination and global exception handling.

--------

## 🚀 Technologies

- Java 17
- Spring Boot
- Spring Security (JWT)
- Spring Data JPA
- PostgreSQL
- Maven

---

## 🔐 Features

- User Registration & Login (JWT)
- Role-based Authorization (USER / ADMIN)
- Create, Update, Delete Story
- Publish / Unpublish Story
- Pagination & Search
- Global Exception Handling
- Clean DTO Architecture

---

## API Endpoints

# Authentication
- POST /api/auth/register
- POST /api/auth/login

#  Stories
- GET /api/stories?page=0&size=10
- GET /api/stories/{id}
- POST /api/stories
- PUT /api/stories/{id}
- DELETE /api/stories/{id}
- PUT /api/stories/{id}/publish
- PUT /api/stories/{id}/unpublish

---

# Architecture

- Entity Layer
- DTO Layer (Request / Response)
- Service Layer
- Security Layer (JWT Filter)
- Global Exception Handler

---

# Security

- JWT Authentication
- Role-based Authorization
- Owner-based Access Control
- Stateless Session Management

---

# Database

This project uses PostgreSQL as the primary database.

You need to create a database named:

storyapp

Update your username and password inside:

src/main/resources/application.properties


## ▶️ How to Run

```bash
mvn clean install
mvn spring-boot:run
